The drag and diffusion coefficients for $\Lambda_c$ as a function of temperature were also analyzed in Ref.~\cite{Ghosh:2014oia}. 
In this work the transport coefficients were obtained by means of two approaches, using the scattering lengths of the 
different $\Lambda_c$-light meson system or the energy-dependent Born terms (or interaction kernels), without unitarization. It was found that 
the coefficients are smaller in size than the ones reported in the present paper. Apart from differences in the kernel of 
the interaction, we conclude that the role of unitarization is important for the correct determination of the transport 
coefficients due to the presence of resonant states, that enhance the cross section, and therefore, the transport coefficients themselves. 


